            "extractedText": "ENGLISH\nXI-English (MCQs), Pagell 89\nUnit# 01\nDEMOCRATIC CITIZENSHIP\nQuaid on 11\" August , 1947\nNote: Read the statements and encircle the right option.\n* national level\nThe Quaid-e-Azam was speaking to the Constituent Assembly at\n* regional level * global level\nThe main function of the Constituent Assembly was to\n* make country as example\n*provincial level\nmake constitution\n* honour assembly members\n3.\n* practice constitution\n* discrimination\nAccording to the Quaid-e-Azam, 'Cyclonic revolution\" meant a wave of\n* revolt\n* elections\n4.\nThe main task of the Govt., according to the Quaid-e-Azam is to\n* legislation\n* make constitution for provinces\n* curb bribery\n* stop black marketing\n* make law and order\n5.\nAccording to the Quaid-e-Azam, the poisonous thing is\n* corruption\n* nepotism\n* black-marketing\n* law and order situation\n6.\nThe colossal crime monster as stated in the text is\n* the law\n* black marketing * favoritism\n7.\nOn I1\" August 1947, Quaid-e Azam was speaking to the\n* bribery\n* already functioning assembly\n* whole nation\n* first legislative body\n* members of the provincial body.\nThe first legislative body was bestowed with\n* with full powers\n* with limited powers\n* to only make legislative powers\n* with only powers to curb bribery\nThe thing that was already prevailing in the sub-continent after partition was.\n* bribery\n* foodstuff\n* nepotism\n* starvation\n10. The guided principles of the Quaid-e-Azam Muhammad Ali Jinnah are\n* support & cooperation\n* justice & fair play\n* prejudice & honour\n* angularity of majority & minority",
