            "extractedText": "ONGLISH\nXI-English (MCQo). Pages 88\nUnit# 01\nDEMOCRATIC CITIZENSHIP\nQuaid on 11\" August, 1947\nNote: Read the statements and encircle the right option.\na national level!\nThe Quaid-e-Azam wis speaking do the Constituent Assembly al\n* regional level * global level\nThe main function of the Constituent Assembly was 1o.\n* make country as example\n*provincial level\n• make constitution\n* honour assembly members\n* practice constitution\nJ.\n* discrimination\nAccording 1o the Quaid-e-Azam, 'Cyclonic revolution' meant a wave of\nrevolt\n* clections\nThe main task of the Govl., according to the Quaid-e-Azam is to\n* legislation\n* make constitution for provinces\n* curb bribery\n* stop black marketing\nAccording to the Quaid-e-Azam, the poisonous thing is-\nmake law and order\n* corruption\n* nepotism\n* black-marketing\n* law and order situation\nThe colossal crime monster as stated in the text is.\n* the law\nblack marketing\n* favoritism\n* bribery\n7. On 11'# August 1947, Quaid-e Azam was speaking to the _\n* already functioning assembly\n* first legislative body\nwhole nation\n* members of the provincial body.\n8.\nThe first legislative body was bestowed with\nwith full powers\n* with Limited powers\n* to only make legislative powers\n* with only powers to curb bribery\n2. The thing that was already prevailing in the sub-continent after partition was\n* bribery\n*foodstuff\n* nepotism\n* starvation\n10. The guided principles of the Quaid-e-Azam Muhammad Ali Jinnah are\n* support & cooperation\n*\njustice & fair play\n* prejudice & honour\n* angularity of majority & minority",
